PLANTS OF TENNESSEE, U.S.A.

*Galax urceolata* (Poiret) Brummitt
[= *G. aphylla* of authors, not L.]

Blount County: NW slope of Chilhowee Mountain; 4.8 km (3 miles) up Happy Valley Road from intersection with Six Mile Road. Elevation ca. 770 meters. Mixed *Quercus*, *Carya*, *Nyssa* forest with *Acer pensylvanicum*. Flowers white; visited by bumblebees and syrphid flies.

D. E. Boufford, S. A. Spongberg & P. S. White
